A man was declared dead by ER24 paramedics in Strydom Street in Potchefstroom, North West, on Saturday. Upon arrival at the scene paramedics found the man laying on the pavement under a tree, spokeswoman Chitra Bodasing-Harduth said. Sadly, he showed no signs of life and was declared dead. There were no visible signs of injury. The exact cause of death is unknown. Authorities are on [the] scene, she said.